cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with learning Mahanalobis distance metrics in a high-dimensional feature space for face verification and retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of ensemble metric learning, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of pairwise or triplet constraints generated from training samples, indicating the use of supervised learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with multimedia data, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the accuracy and efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which can be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
